This paper proposes a deep-learning framework for semantic segmentation and image restoration in adverse environmental conditions. The paper focuses on computer vision tasks, specifically semantic segmentation and image restoration, which are typically categorized under cs.CV. The proposed approach involves the use of deep learning techniques, which are commonly associated with cs.AI and cs.LG. The paper also involves the use of image processing techniques, which can be categorized under cs.MM. Finally, the paper involves the use of guidance and adaptation techniques, which can be categorized under cs.GR.
